<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

  <body>
    <metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
      <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-groups" />
      <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-stats" />
    </metal:leftportlets>

    <metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
      <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-preflangs" />
    </metal:rightportlets>

    <div metal:fill-slot="main">

      <h1>About Launchpad Translations</h1>

      <p>Launchpad Translations is a Web-based system for translating open source software into
        any language. All you need to start translating is a Web browser, a good
        knowledge of the application you are translating, and a knowledge of
        English.
      </p>

      <h2>How do I get my software translated in Launchpad?</h2>
      <p>
        Launchpad can let people translate any open-source software that uses the
        <a href="http://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/"
        ><abbr>GNU</abbr> gettext</a> system for internationalization.
        For more information, see the
        <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/TranslationsImportPolicy">import
        policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Join the Launchpad Translations community</h2>

      <p>
        To participate in the development and testing of Launchpad Translations,        join the <a
        href="http://lists.canonical.com/mailman/listinfo/launchpad-users">
	Launchpad users mailing list</a>, where we discuss new 
        features, bugs and other issues.
      </p>

      <ul class="info">
        <li>
          <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/LaunchpadTranslationsFAQ">More about Launchpad Translations</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

    </div>
    <div metal:fill-slot="help">
      <p>
        From this page, you will be able to find resources about how to start
	using Launchpad Translations. Either to help translating applications 
	or to get your application translated by others.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
